HEADWORD: Inferiority
<hw>In*fe`ri*or"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>inf⟦eacute⟧riorit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being
inferior; a lower state or condition; <as>as, <ex>inferiority</ex> of
rank, of talents, of age, of worth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A deep sense of our own great <qex>inferiority</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inferiorly</ent>⟦br⟧
